        {
            "title": "LIPSE: Learning from innovation in public sector environments",
            "date": {
                "start": {
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2013
                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 1,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2013
                }
            },
            "description": "Funded by the EU's FP7 framework, the LIPSE project identifies drivers and barriers to successful social innovation in the public sector. Through studying social innovation and co-creation practices and processes in 11 European countries and 7 policy sectors, LIPSE will create and disseminate essential knowledge about public innovation. The project will not only analyse the drivers and barriers social innovation, but also the actual outcomes of these innovations. To encourage social innovation, governments are setting up new collaborative arrangements with citizens, non-governmental organizations and companies. The emphasis lies on co-creation and coproduction. Social innovation offers the chance to reconsider existing practices, creating more opportunities for local bottom-up initiatives. ",
