                    "company": "Erasmus University Rotterdam",
                    "description": "My cum laude PhD-thesis focused on the problem of professionals with new policies they have to implement.  \n\nToday, many public professionals feel estranged from these policies. For example, many Dutch secondary school teachers cannot identify with the policy program called the Second Phase. This is of concern as, for effective implementation, some identification with the policy is required. \n\nI examined this problem by using the innovative concept of 'policy alienation'. One product is a measurement instrument to examine the degree of policy alienation of professionals. This can be used by policymakers, leaders and managers to assess and enhance the support for a new policy.\n\nTitle PhD Thesis: Policy Alienation: Analyzing the experiences of public professionals with new policies.",
